        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &quot;Mukhyamantri Nahri Kendra&quot; was launched by the Tribal Development Department, Government of Gujarat. The scheme aims to empower tribal women by providing them with livelihood opportunities through women-run centers. These centers promote the sale of tribal dishes and home-made products, thereby improving income and living standards. Under this scheme, tribal women-run groups receive a subsidy covering 50% of project costs and the remaining 50% as a loan at a concessional interest rate. \n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "> **Monetary Benefit**\n\n\n- 50% of the project cost or ₹5,00,000, whichever is less, provided as subsidy.\n- The remaining 50% of the project cost is provided as a loan.\n\n> ***Subsidy Disbursement***\n\n\n- Given in two installments – 60% in the first installment and 40% in the second installment.\n\n> ***Interest Rate***\n\n\n- Loan at 4% per annum.\n\n> ***Repayment***\n\n\n- Loan (excluding subsidy) must be repaid in 20 equal installments over 5 years, including interest.\n- Option to repay earlier is allowed.\n\n> ***Beneficiary Contribution***\n\n\n- No upfront contribution required from the beneficiary.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme empowers tribal women by providing them with livelihood opportunities through women-run centers. These centers promote the sale of tribal dishes and home-made products, thereby improving income and living standards. Tribal women-run groups receive a subsidy covering 50% of project cost.",
        "exclusions_md": "",
